1
00:01:58,440 --> 00:02:01,280
{\an8}But I'm just not ready to face
the same problems again.

2
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:08,280
{\an8}Please just return
to your fiancée and your mom.

3
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,800
{\an8}Mook.

4
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,360
{\an8}- Boss!
- Boss!

5
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:23,880
{\an8}You told me to compete with you, remember?

6
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:29,400
{\an8}…which is that Bell
is the fiancée of Mr. Thee,

7
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:31,040
{\an8}an executive at TJ Group.

8
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:36,160
{\an8}We're also about to have great news
to share with you all very soon.

9
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,160
MOOK

10
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,720
I've driven Mrs. Anna to her place.

11
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,000
I still can't get ahold of Mook.

12
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:19,280
She might not want to talk to you for now

13
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,360
because the press conference today

14
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:24,520
probably got published on social media
by some agencies already.

15
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,920
I want to know where Mook is right now.

16
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,000
Got it.

17
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,880
I'll try to contact her.

18
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,920
Yes, Mr. Chadchai?

19
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,360
Sure.

20
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,280
I'll see you when we sign the contract.

21
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,360
We're here.

22
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:30,280
Do you think this place
could be turned into a chic studio?

23
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:34,040
I want to make it my office
for when I design clothes.

24
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:37,680
It'll also be a spot for emerging
designers to showcase their work.

25
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,600
Would this be a good spot?

26
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:46,680
But I think this place
would work better as an office.

27
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:52,680
Why don't you ask Mr. Thee for advice
or ask for a room at The One?

28
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,520
Why should I ask him?

29
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,600
I can make my own decisions.

30
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,400
This has nothing to do with Thee anyway.

31
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,160
Can you come with me?

32
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:06,240
I'm not good at negotiating prices

33
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:08,640
or handling the details in the agreements.

34
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,040
I'm busy.

35
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:22,360
Come on in.

36
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,680
Do you like this?

37
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:30,080
It looks pretty good. What do you think?

38
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,120
Maybe this one.

39
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:41,320
Here's the lease agreement.

40
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,560
Thank you.

41
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:51,400
I may need to review
all the terms on here again.

42
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,880
I may need to make
some adjustments or additions.

43
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,440
Of course.

44
00:05:55,520 --> 00:06:01,440
Would you and your girlfriend
like a short-term or long-term lease?

45
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,680
Can we discuss it first?

46
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,360
We'll let you know soon.

47
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,560
Sure.

48
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,800
Do you like this place, honey?

49
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:46,440
May, why don't I see that guy?

50
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:47,960
Will he really show up?

51
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,200
He will.

52
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:52,320
Ms. Ploy said he's here regularly.

53
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:57,160
Stay calm, or you'll look panicked.

54
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:46,320
He really came. What do we do now?

55
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:51,360
Don't be nervous. Just follow the plan.

56
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,600
Excuse me.

57
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,400
Can I sit with you?

58
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,280
Sure.

59
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:01,360
Hey, have we met before?

60
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,920
That's an old one.

61
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:07,320
Why? If we never met,
would you not want to talk?

62
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:10,880
Of course I would.

63
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:16,160
Who would let a pretty girl like you
stay so lonely?

64
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,800
Cheers.

65
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,360
KEMTIT

66
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:40,360
<i>He took the bait. What do we do now?</i>

67
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:50,280
Mr. Pitak, are you sure Mook came here?

68
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:54,320
<i>Yes, Mr. Thee. Mr. Suetrong said</i>
<i>the whole team went there.</i>

69
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,720
Top's here now. He's talking to May.

70
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,880
{\an8}MOOK

71
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,120
{\an8}<i>How's the situation?</i>

72
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,640
<i>Everything going according to plan?</i>

73
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,400
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

74
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,440
Sorry, that's my car key.

75
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:36,440
Hold on. I can get it for you.

76
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,320
Thank you.

77
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,720
What?

78
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:52,040
My dear client,
why are you calling me now?

79
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:55,240
Excuse me. I dropped something here.

80
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,000
You wanna book more?

81
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,520
MS. BANGORN: CALL BACK ASAP
I'D LIKE TO BOOK MORE TOURS

82
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,640
I'm not sure if it's there.
Can you help me find it?

83
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,320
Found it. Thank you.

84
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,480
Here it is.

85
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,640
Hello, Ms. Bangorn?

86
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:22,960
Yes, Ms. Bangorn.

87
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,840
It's really loud where I'm at.

88
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:29,120
Can you give me a moment?
I'm outside right now. Please hang on.

89
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,560
Mook, what should we do?

90
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:51,720
Tell May to try and lure him
into taking her to his usual place.

91
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:55,320
We'll hurry and follow them there,
so we can get inside and find evidence.

92
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,720
Whan, go with May too, just to be safe.

93
00:11:58,320 --> 00:11:59,440
Sure.

94
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:06,800
What if Top hurts Ms. May and Whan?

95
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:10,800
If it goes according to our plan,
he won't be able to touch them.

96
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,320
You're no lightweight, huh?

97
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,440
You've had so many with me.

98
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,000
I'm not as good as you, though.

99
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:31,520
You had so many drinks,
yet you still look normal.

100
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:37,800
I'm a little tipsy now.

101
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,240
One more?

102
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:44,760
Sure.

103
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,480
Are you good?

104
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,760
No! Her phone's here…

105
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:56,840
Whan, where's May?!

106
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:59,800
Kemtit! I… I only

107
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,560
went outside to call Mook for a bit,
but now they're gone.

108
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:07,840
Why haven't those three come out yet?

109
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,560
Let me go find them.

110
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,880
Whan, why are you still inside?

111
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:20,680
May's gone. And so is that guy.

112
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,520
What? May's gone?

113
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:28,280
- Top!
- Where?

114
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,480
Hey, look!

115
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:32,720
Top took Ms. May already!

116
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,800
Whan, hurry and call the cops.

117
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,440
Then follow me right away.

118
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:40,440
I'll share you my location.

119
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,400
Okay, got it.

120
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:02,040
FUN PLAZA

121
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:32,120
It's strange.

122
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,000
Why'd Ms. May agree
to get in his car so easily?

123
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,200
No!

124
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:46,320
- What?
- What?

125
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,160
Why didn't the car in front of us go?!

126
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,120
Why'd it have to turn red now?!

127
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,560
We lost them. What do we do, Mook?

128
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,840
<i>Where should we go to next?</i>

129
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,960
How about my condo?

130
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:16,880
Let's go to my place instead.

131
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:20,560
I assure you you'll like it.

132
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,840
I know where
that scumbag's taking Ms. May.

133
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,120
Mook, it's green now. Go!

134
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:30,160
Who the hell is it?

135
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,920
- What?!
- Your drink, sir.

136
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,160
What the hell?

137
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,520
- Quick, let's go!
- Hey!

138
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,920
Ms. May! Ms. May?

139
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,960
Can you hear me? Wake up, Ms. May!

140
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,880
- Ms. May!
- He really did set up a camera!

141
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,600
Ms. May, get up slowly.

142
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,840
- Ms. May!
- Now you're asking for it!

143
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:19,680
‪Let go!

144
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:20,920
- Let go!
- Stop!

145
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,520
- Let go of her!
- Let go!

146
00:18:23,360 --> 00:18:24,640
- No! Mook!
- Mook!

147
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:31,160
- Get May out of here! Hurry!
- Ms. May!

148
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,360
Let's go!

149
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,880
- Let's go.
- Hurry!

150
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:36,280
Go! Be careful!

151
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:37,440
Let's go.

152
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,480
- No!
- You're really asking for it, huh?

153
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:41,040
Let go!

154
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:47,280
- Come here.
- Let go! No!

155
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:50,200
No!

156
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,160
Let go!

157
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,280
Let go…

158
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,600
Mook!

159
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:14,040
Stop! This is the police!

160
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,440
I didn't do anything!

161
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:18,520
We got a report that you lured
a woman here to assault her.

162
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:19,880
- I don't know anything.
- Move!

163
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,360
- I didn't do it!
- Let's go!

164
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,280
Please let me go!

165
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:24,280
- Come on!
- Let me go. I didn't do it!

166
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:25,480
- Move.
- Officer!

167
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:26,960
- Come on.
- Please let me go!

168
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,000
Move!

169
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,920
- May, May!
- Sis!

170
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:32,680
May!

171
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:35,920
Are you okay, May? May!

172
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,600
- Kem…
- May!

173
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,760
Kemtit.

174
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:44,080
Go with May.
I'll stay here and look after Mook.

175
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,000
Okay.

176
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:47,800
- Take her bag.
- May.

177
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:49,360
- Watch out.
- Okay.

178
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:50,760
- Please mind your head.
- Okay.

179
00:19:57,360 --> 00:19:59,120
Stop resisting!

180
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,200
Move it.

181
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,400
Just watch your backs.

182
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,080
I'm coming for you all.

183
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,320
We have solid evidence.

184
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,640
No one can help you now.

185
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:13,800
Go pay for your crimes in jail.

186
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,760
We'll need you all at the station
for statements.

187
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,200
- Of course.
- Let's go!

188
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:21,480
Move!

189
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:24,360
Get in!

190
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,360
You did it, Ploy.

191
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,960
Mook, are you okay?

192
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,760
Mook,

193
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:09,640
you're bleeding.

194
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:14,080
It's just a scratch. I'll be fine.

195
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:20,600
Top's arrested now.

196
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,600
You two won't have to be afraid anymore.

197
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:30,040
Mook, worry about yourself
instead of others for once, would you?

198
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:34,120
Let's get her to a hospital.

199
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,240
- Let's go.
- Okay.

200
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:38,240
Let's go.

201
00:21:56,960 --> 00:22:02,120
Yes? Hello, Boss. Mook is injured.

202
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:13,080
Just fess up.

203
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:15,040
We've got solid evidence here.

204
00:22:17,080 --> 00:22:18,680
That's just part of it.

205
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,760
There are many other videos, Officer.

206
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:25,040
What are you on about?

207
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:26,520
I've never done that stuff!

208
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:29,920
You caught me with a girl at a hotel
and got jealous,

209
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,880
so you made all this up to accuse me.

210
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,920
Why are you doing this to me?

211
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,800
Stop pretending to be a good person, Top.

212
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,840
Everyone knows your true colors now!

213
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,320
Officer,

214
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:44,880
there's enough evidence
for him to be locked up now, right?

215
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,080
Don't listen to her! She's lying.

216
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,000
She's just mad I cheated.

217
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:51,440
You're the one who's lying!

218
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,640
Your evil ends here, Top.

219
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:56,880
I'd like to file a report against him too.

220
00:22:56,960 --> 00:23:00,080
He filmed me and threatened me.

221
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:02,040
He assaulted me too.

222
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:05,040
I'd like to file a report too.

223
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,000
Fine!

224
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,040
File your reports.

225
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:10,640
I'm not scared.

226
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,000
My family's rich. I'll be fine.

227
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,520
Just watch your backs.

228
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:17,440
I'll make sure you pay!

229
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:20,960
Officer, why are you grabbing me?

230
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,120
Let me go!

231
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:25,640
Just watch yourselves, bitches! Officer!

232
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:19,120
NURSE - ASSESSMENT ROOM 1

233
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:21,960
I'm alright now. You should go home.

234
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:25,360
You know what you did
was really dangerous, right?

235
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,960
What if he hurt you or if he had a gun?

236
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,480
What would you do?

237
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:32,800
But it's over now, and I'm alright too.

238
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,520
You call this "alright"?

239
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:39,120
Did he have to hit your vital organs
for you to realize?

240
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:43,080
Don't do this again, Mook.

241
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,720
If someone's got to be hurt,

242
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:49,600
it has to be me, not you.

243
00:24:57,880 --> 00:24:59,000
Mook.

244
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:04,080
- Boss.
- Bell?

245
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,920
Why are you here, Thee?

246
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,120
Are you hurt? Are you wounded?

247
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:20,280
Mook, are you badly hurt?

248
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,320
It's just a scratch.

249
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:26,920
Nothing bad. What about Ploy and Khim?

250
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:30,240
They're at the station,
giving the police more information.

251
00:25:31,080 --> 00:25:32,440
I want to see my friends.

252
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:33,680
Can you give me a ride, Boss?

253
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:35,320
Of course.

254
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:38,080
I'll take care of her, Mr. Thee.

255
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:39,960
Don't worry.

256
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,160
Mook.

257
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:49,480
Does it hurt a lot?

258
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,520
Ploy, are you okay?

259
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,840
VISION - BE LOYAL, ENSURE
OUR NATION'S SECURITY, EARN PEOPLE'S TRUST

260
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,520
I did it.

261
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:30,560
I dealt with the scumbag who hurt us.

262
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:34,120
I did it, Khim.

263
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:39,960
Good job. You're the best, Ploy.

264
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,440
Ploy, Khim,

265
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,240
is everything alright?

266
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:50,800
It's all over. You're all safe now.

267
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:54,160
- You're okay now.
- Yeah.

268
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:13,600
{\an8}ARRESTED FOR VIDEO BLACKMAIL

269
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,280
{\an8}POLICE HAVE ARRESTED
MR. UDOM MONGKOLPANICH

270
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:16,920
{\an8}WHO'S SECRETLY FILMED AND BLACKMAILED
MANY WOMEN. MANY MORE ARE FILING REPORTS

271
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:34,200
Pa, Ma, I'm sorry.

272
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:40,520
No.

273
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:43,880
Why are you apologizing, Ploy?

274
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:49,680
I'm the one who should be apologizing

275
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:53,280
for introducing you

276
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:56,560
to such an evil guy.

277
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:59,800
That's why you're in this much pain.

278
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:02,440
I'm sorry, honey.

279
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,760
No, Ma…

280
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:11,520
It's okay, honey.

281
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,320
Don't blame yourself, Ma.

282
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:16,720
Let's just forget about it.

283
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,640
It's over now.

284
00:28:20,360 --> 00:28:21,640
Don't cry, Ma.

285
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,280
Move back in with us, honey.

286
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:25,280
Now that it's all over the news,

287
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,480
what do you plan to do?

288
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:33,240
If you don't want to see anyone yet,

289
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:35,320
just ask for some time off,

290
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:37,640
or you can quit your job too.

291
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:40,080
Then we'll make plans

292
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:42,240
on what to do next.

293
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,920
I'm really sorry.

294
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:37,440
Khim,

295
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:40,560
I saw the news about you.

296
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:42,600
Are you okay?

297
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,960
What you saw on the news is true.

298
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:51,040
I'll make sure he pays for his crimes.

299
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:56,600
I never thought
you'd also be one of his victims.

300
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:59,520
People these days are so scary.

301
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:03,080
They can seem so nice,
but they're hiding their evil side.

302
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:08,520
It was partly my fault.

303
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:14,880
I was too reckless and pleasure-seeking.

304
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:18,280
Otherwise, I never would've got into this.

305
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:26,400
I heard they're setting up a committee
to look into your case.

306
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:30,200
I think it'd be really unfair
if you got fired.

307
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:37,120
Hey.

308
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:29,480
Bell!

309
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:31,000
- Hi, Thee.
- You're here so early.

310
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:37,240
Sit down, Thee.

311
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:38,680
What's wrong?

312
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:41,160
I wanted to ask you about something.

313
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:43,560
You know Mr. Anapat too?

314
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:46,840
Of course. Mr. Anapat

315
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:49,200
is the CEO of A Round Trip Travel,

316
00:31:49,280 --> 00:31:50,800
my hotel's partner.

317
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:54,320
How about you? How'd you two meet?

318
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,600
Just a coincidence.

319
00:31:57,800 --> 00:32:00,000
How come you came with Mr. Pat last night?

320
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:02,120
It's a long story, Thee.

321
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:06,720
Yesterday I saw Mr. Anapat and Mook.
They seemed really close.

322
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:09,200
Does he have a crush on her too?

323
00:32:11,080 --> 00:32:13,960
I don't know. If you want to know,
you should ask him yourself.

324
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:18,840
Where are you going?

325
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:21,440
I'm heading out for a meeting.

326
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:22,440
Is there anything else?

327
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:42,160
Here it is. I got it from a famous place.

328
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:44,000
I had to wait in a long line.

329
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:46,960
They say it's super yummy.

330
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:49,720
Please eat up, so you'll feel better.

331
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:54,120
She's smiling!

332
00:32:56,360 --> 00:32:58,160
I got so scared last night.

333
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:00,360
I'm glad you and Mook are okay.

334
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:03,440
That jerk!

335
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:05,280
How dare he hurt May!

336
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:07,840
I'll kill him with my own hands!

337
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:13,760
Well, if we let an evil guy like him go,

338
00:33:13,840 --> 00:33:16,400
he'd go on and hurt more people.

339
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:19,600
Aw, just admit you're worried about her.

340
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:23,440
You know me too well. Cheers!

341
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:28,840
- What?!
- Mook!

342
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,680
Why are you here?
Wait till your wound's healed!

343
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,240
It's just a scratch.

344
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:35,280
I wasn't hurt that badly.

345
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:36,760
May, how are you?

346
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:38,400
Why didn't you take some time off?

347
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:39,960
Mook,

348
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:42,040
thank you so much.

349
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:46,240
I'm doing better now.

350
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:50,760
I'm still a little paranoid and sad.

351
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:54,400
I've never been drugged before in my life.

352
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:57,840
It was my very first time.

353
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:59,880
I got all dazed and dizzy.

354
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:01,680
I wasn't in control at all.

355
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:06,400
I'm just glad you're okay. I'm sorry.

356
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:10,320
And I really appreciate you all

357
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:12,679
for taking a risk to help catch Top.

358
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:16,280
I should be thanking you. You too.

359
00:34:16,360 --> 00:34:18,560
- Thank you.
- Of course.

360
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:22,159
Mook.

361
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:30,320
I've got to go.

362
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:33,679
See you.

363
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:38,199
Hello.

364
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:48,080
How are you holding up?

365
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:50,400
I…

366
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,440
I'm alright now.

367
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,120
Please excuse me. I've got work to do.

368
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:06,920
I'm really worried about you, you know?

369
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:09,440
Don't risk your life like that again.

370
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:14,360
I wouldn't know what to do
if something were to happen to you.

371
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:27,440
Is there anything else?

372
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:29,440
Something work-related?

373
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:32,240
Yes.

374
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:37,560
I came to tell you to get ready to go
to Narin Beach Resort with me tomorrow.

375
00:35:38,760 --> 00:35:41,920
Why? It's not nearly time
for the event yet.

376
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:44,800
I'm signing a contract
with Ms. Narin tomorrow.

377
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:49,160
That's got nothing to do with me.

378
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:50,720
Why do I need to go?

379
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:54,440
I wanted to adjust some of the plans
for the event we're organizing there.

380
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:56,800
You're in charge of that, no?

381
00:35:57,680 --> 00:36:00,600
Therefore, you have to come
with me tomorrow.

382
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:23,280
You look so pretty.

383
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:27,040
- There you are.
- I'm here!

384
00:36:31,760 --> 00:36:33,600
Thank you so much, you guys.

385
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:36,560
I couldn't have done it without you.

386
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,800
Once again, I'm sorry, Ploy.

387
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:44,600
Thank you for understanding.

388
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:51,080
Friends should be there
for each other anyway.

389
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:54,640
Sometimes we might argue or fight,

390
00:36:55,480 --> 00:36:57,040
but we'd never leave each other.

391
00:37:01,360 --> 00:37:02,800
Oh, Mook,

392
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:05,800
I saw the news about Mr. Thee's fiancée.

393
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,120
What's that about?

394
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:09,320
Why'd you never tell us about it?

395
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,400
I just found out not long ago too.

396
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:22,640
If he can get engaged, then you can too.

397
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,120
Come again?

398
00:37:26,640 --> 00:37:27,800
Mr. Pat, of course!

399
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:32,000
You and Mr. Pat
are perfect for each other.

400
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:35,320
Everyone's rooting for you
to be together, so just date for real.

401
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:40,640
Mr. Pat's my boss, my brother,
and a good friend of mine.

402
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:44,640
He's also very understanding
and gives great advice,

403
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:48,720
but I've never had feelings for him.

404
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:52,560
And I think he sees me in the same way.

405
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:59,000
Are you okay, Mook?

406
00:37:59,080 --> 00:38:01,040
You got your heart broken again.

407
00:38:01,120 --> 00:38:02,880
I'm worried about you.

408
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:05,200
I'm okay.

409
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:09,080
Maybe I'm lucky in games
and unlucky in love.

410
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:14,560
But either way, I have a mom
and a daughter who love me very much.

411
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:17,400
And I also have you two, my best friends,

412
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,240
who support me with everything.

413
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:25,720
Come on. Give me your hand.

414
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:31,160
From now on,

415
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:35,080
no matter what we may face,
we'll get through it together.

416
00:38:36,640 --> 00:38:37,640
Okay?

417
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:38,600
Okay.

418
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:40,880
Good. I love you two.

419
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:48,480
As if you haven't seen it before.

420
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:52,440
- Your dress slayed both of us.
- Can I pull off sexy too?

421
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:54,440
Here we go.

422
00:38:54,520 --> 00:38:56,440
- Here we go.
- Try it. Embrace it.

423
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:57,720
- You think so?
- Yeah.

424
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:59,760
I'm trying to reset myself.

425
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,600
Come on in.

426
00:39:06,600 --> 00:39:08,120
Someone's here to see you, Mr. Pat.

427
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:10,960
Come on in.

428
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:13,200
It's you!

429
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:20,200
What's Mr. Thee's fiancée doing here?

430
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:22,960
Yeah. Why'd she have to come
all the way here to see our boss?

431
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:26,880
- Oh, could it be--
- Hey!

432
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:27,880
Quiet!

433
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:33,760
Could it be she's here
to end our contract?

434
00:39:33,840 --> 00:39:36,480
She might be mad at Mr. Thee
for liking Mook,

435
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:39,000
so much so, she's ending our contract.

436
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:42,240
I hope it's not that bad.

437
00:39:43,720 --> 00:39:46,360
Let's not jump to conclusions here.

438
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:49,880
Why else would she come
to our office then, Mr. Suetrong?

439
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:56,240
What?

440
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:59,520
KOH CHANG - CHIANG MAI - KRABI - KOH LIPE

441
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:00,520
Mr. Suetrong!

442
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:10,880
How'd you find this place?

443
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:13,160
It isn't that hard, really.

444
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:14,960
I just had to ask Mr. Pitak.

445
00:40:17,520 --> 00:40:19,600
Are you that surprised that I'm here?

446
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:28,600
You like Ms. Mook, don't you?

447
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:35,640
I asked Mr. Thee, and he told me
to ask you myself.

448
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:38,720
Why do you want to know?

449
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:41,160
Well, I wanted to get closer to you,

450
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:43,760
but if you like Ms. Mook, then that's it.

451
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:49,720
What if I told you
I didn't have feelings for Mook?

452
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:55,880
Then I'll get to know you,

453
00:40:55,960 --> 00:40:57,640
so we can become closer.

454
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:12,840
Bee, there's something I want you to see.

455
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:22,560
Isn't this Prao's husband, Pat?

456
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:25,920
It's him, right? I happened to be
viewing the same building that day,

457
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:28,600
and I saw Mr. Anapat with Ms. Bella,

458
00:41:28,680 --> 00:41:31,560
who publicly confirmed
her engagement with Mr. Thee recently.

459
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:36,800
You should let me cover this story.

460
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:39,400
Mr. Pat's about to enter politics.

461
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:42,160
If you wrote about it,
you might get into trouble.

462
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:43,920
Is that so?

463
00:41:45,080 --> 00:41:47,640
Ms. Prao's father is a big shot.

464
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:50,240
He wouldn't let anyone
discredit his son-in-law so easily.

465
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:13,440
Who's the girl?

466
00:42:13,520 --> 00:42:14,880
Her name's Bella.

467
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:16,400
She's Mr. Thee's fiancée.

468
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:19,360
Mr. Thee's fiancée?

469
00:42:20,360 --> 00:42:21,800
Why was she seen with Pat?

470
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:23,400
How'd they meet?

471
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:27,080
<i>I know, right? When I saw</i>
<i>the photo, I was surprised too.</i>

472
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,840
<i>They seem really close too.</i>

473
00:42:31,560 --> 00:42:36,200
Thank God it was my junior reporter
who saw them

474
00:42:36,280 --> 00:42:38,080
because if this photo got out,

475
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:41,520
<i>it could damage</i>
<i>Mr. Pat's career in politics.</i>

476
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:45,280
Don't worry, I'll reward you for this.

477
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,640
Thanks for looking out for me.

478
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:51,480
It'd be great
if you could keep an eye on him.

479
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:53,160
<i>Of course, Prao.</i>

480
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:13,160
<i>If you don't want to see anyone yet,</i>

481
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:15,800
<i>just ask for some time off,</i>

482
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:17,840
<i>or you can quit your job too.</i>

483
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:19,960
<i>Then we'll make plans</i>

484
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:22,400
<i>on what to do next.</i>

485
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:29,160
ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT

486
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:46,440
We're happy for you
for getting through it, Ploy.

487
00:43:47,440 --> 00:43:49,560
We wish you lots of happiness from now on.

488
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:55,080
Here you go.

489
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:03,560
What's all this about?

490
00:44:03,640 --> 00:44:05,280
Haven't you been online?

491
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:08,040
So many pages posted about your story.

492
00:44:08,120 --> 00:44:09,880
Everyone's rooting for you

493
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:13,000
for standing up to a scumbag
like that guy.

494
00:44:13,560 --> 00:44:15,160
You're really brave, Ploy.

495
00:44:15,240 --> 00:44:18,880
If it happened to me,
I don't know if I'd have your courage.

496
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:22,160
You did great.

497
00:44:22,240 --> 00:44:23,880
- You did great.
- You rock!

498
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:31,720
Woman of the year.

499
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:33,440
Great job.

500
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:49,440
What's this about?

501
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:51,920
Why'd our clients cancel on us?

502
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:53,840
It's a huge group of them too, no?

503
00:44:55,760 --> 00:44:57,360
Who's in charge of this tour group?

504
00:44:57,960 --> 00:44:59,080
It's Ms. Usa.

505
00:45:01,920 --> 00:45:03,440
Go get her in here, then.

506
00:45:04,120 --> 00:45:05,960
She hasn't come in yet.

507
00:45:06,040 --> 00:45:08,400
I tried to contact her,
but she turned off her phone.

508
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:14,560
And our clients also complained
that our service isn't good like before,

509
00:45:14,640 --> 00:45:15,960
when Ms. Mook was still here.

510
00:45:22,240 --> 00:45:24,200
Go. You can leave now.

511
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:29,000
I brought you some dim sum.

512
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:34,480
What's wrong? You look stressed.

513
00:45:44,160 --> 00:45:47,640
Are you crazy? No way!

514
00:45:47,720 --> 00:45:51,160
You can't ask Mook for help!

515
00:45:51,240 --> 00:45:53,560
But it's seriously bad this time, Ma.

516
00:45:53,640 --> 00:45:55,320
We just lost a huge group of clients.

517
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:59,320
That's a big loss,
and we're already struggling.

518
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:00,880
No money coming in, just going out.

519
00:46:00,960 --> 00:46:03,720
No, no, no! Don't say that.

520
00:46:03,800 --> 00:46:06,080
Our company's great, and we're prospering.

521
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:07,200
Keep repeating that.

522
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:10,320
Prospering downhill, more like.

523
00:46:10,880 --> 00:46:13,520
Our old clients keep leaving,
and we have no new clients.

524
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:15,160
I don't know what to do, Ma.

525
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:30,080
Ask Usa to help you find
more clients, then.

526
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:32,480
Usa, you say?

527
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:34,280
Our clients don't want her anymore!

528
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:37,240
She's rude,
and she gives horrible service.

529
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:40,680
- It was so different when we had Mook.
- Stop it!

530
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:44,400
Stop praising her already.

531
00:46:44,480 --> 00:46:48,280
I won't allow you to ask
for her help, no matter what.

532
00:46:48,360 --> 00:46:50,120
I'll handle this myself.

533
00:46:51,600 --> 00:46:53,320
I'll find you some clients.

534
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:58,200
- Really, Ma?
- Yes.

535
00:46:59,680 --> 00:47:01,240
And remember,

536
00:47:02,640 --> 00:47:06,440
we've got this, even without Mook.

537
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:27,600
- Ms. Mook!
- Hello, Ms. Narin.

538
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:28,680
Hello.

539
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:30,960
My staff told me you've arrived,

540
00:47:31,040 --> 00:47:33,920
so I wanted to welcome you myself
in case you needed something.

541
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:35,400
Thank you.

542
00:47:37,520 --> 00:47:41,440
About that day,
you're feeling better now, right?

543
00:47:47,720 --> 00:47:50,280
Sorry for mentioning it.

544
00:47:50,360 --> 00:47:52,040
I'm just really worried about you.

545
00:47:53,280 --> 00:47:54,880
Thank you, Ms. Narin.

546
00:47:54,960 --> 00:47:57,920
I'm finding the best way out too.

547
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:02,760
But I can't tell how I really feel either.

548
00:48:04,560 --> 00:48:08,280
Have you ever had something
weighing on you, Ms. Narin?

549
00:48:09,880 --> 00:48:10,800
Of course.

550
00:48:14,360 --> 00:48:16,640
- Hello.
- Hello.

551
00:48:17,160 --> 00:48:18,440
Everything's all set.

552
00:48:19,960 --> 00:48:21,720
Then, if you'll excuse me.

553
00:48:21,800 --> 00:48:23,000
Okay.

554
00:48:23,680 --> 00:48:26,240
Mr. Thee said to invite you too, Ms. Mook.

555
00:48:28,880 --> 00:48:30,880
- Sure.
- Let's go together then, Ms. Mook.

556
00:48:30,960 --> 00:48:31,920
Let's go.

557
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:38,000
SIGNATURE
MR. THEECHUDA TEERASU - PARTNER

558
00:48:39,400 --> 00:48:41,120
{\an8}SIGNATURE - MS. NARIN PONGSATORNPITAK

559
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:54,120
I hope you'll remember our promise.

560
00:48:54,720 --> 00:48:55,960
Yes,

561
00:48:56,040 --> 00:48:59,360
I promise to help make this place better.

562
00:49:00,720 --> 00:49:01,840
Thank you.

563
00:49:29,560 --> 00:49:30,680
Where's my phone?

564
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:38,280
Everything's handled now.

565
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:41,040
Not yet. This is just the beginning.

566
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:45,840
- I want all of this resort's shares.
- Don't worry.

567
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:47,400
I'm already talking to them.

568
00:49:48,040 --> 00:49:49,320
There shouldn't be a problem.

569
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:51,800
With the price you offer,

570
00:49:51,880 --> 00:49:53,400
they're all willing to sell.

571
00:49:54,720 --> 00:49:55,600
Good,

572
00:49:56,200 --> 00:49:59,760
if everyone's on board,
I'll leave the rest to you, Mr. Chadchai.

573
00:50:00,560 --> 00:50:01,920
I don't want to waste any time.

574
00:50:03,320 --> 00:50:04,280
Of course, Mr. Thee.

575
00:50:08,520 --> 00:50:10,680
<i>Did Mr. Thee do something</i>
<i>to make you uncomfortable?</i>

576
00:50:11,440 --> 00:50:12,320
Should I go there?

577
00:50:13,200 --> 00:50:14,240
It's okay, Boss.

578
00:50:14,840 --> 00:50:17,880
We mostly just talk about work.
I can handle it.

579
00:50:18,920 --> 00:50:21,600
I'm leaving tomorrow, so don't worry.

580
00:50:22,760 --> 00:50:25,880
Feel free to call me anytime
if something comes up.

581
00:50:26,920 --> 00:50:29,280
Sure, thank you.

582
00:50:41,240 --> 00:50:42,720
<i>What do you want from me?</i>

583
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:45,480
I just want to be sure

584
00:50:45,560 --> 00:50:49,280
that my decision
won't affect anyone's relationship.

585
00:50:50,920 --> 00:50:52,680
I have very few friends.

586
00:50:52,760 --> 00:50:54,880
Almost none, actually.

587
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:58,320
And I feel comfortable talking to you,

588
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:00,680
so I want you to be a friend

589
00:51:00,760 --> 00:51:02,320
who can give me advice.

590
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:06,160
And I want to be sure you're okay
with having me as a friend too.

591
00:51:10,960 --> 00:51:13,680
So, what do you think? Would you mind it?

592
00:51:14,800 --> 00:51:17,160
Won't it affect
your relationship with Mr. Thee?

593
00:51:19,000 --> 00:51:22,800
Because I don't want to damage
anyone's relationship either.

594
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:27,840
Thee and I are just fulfilling our duties.

595
00:51:31,360 --> 00:51:32,880
I think I got my answer.

596
00:51:34,520 --> 00:51:36,400
I'll get out of your hair now. Bye-bye.

597
00:51:57,240 --> 00:51:59,520
{\an8}PRAO

598
00:52:05,840 --> 00:52:06,880
Yes, Prao?

599
00:52:26,240 --> 00:52:27,800
Mr. Thee wanted you to have this.

600
00:52:29,080 --> 00:52:30,240
Thank you.

601
00:52:48,120 --> 00:52:50,080
<i>For our special day,</i>

602
00:52:50,160 --> 00:52:51,960
<i>please come to dinner with me.</i>

603
00:52:52,040 --> 00:52:54,080
<i>I have something important to tell you.</i>

604
00:53:11,160 --> 00:53:13,160
I just wanted to return your stuff.

605
00:53:14,400 --> 00:53:16,840
And don't do this again. It isn't funny.

606
00:53:19,760 --> 00:53:21,240
Calm down, Mook.

607
00:53:22,840 --> 00:53:24,800
I just wanted to clear things up.

608
00:53:25,720 --> 00:53:27,640
I want us to go back to the way we were.

609
00:53:28,240 --> 00:53:29,760
I want you to trust me.

610
00:53:32,800 --> 00:53:34,000
Trust you?

611
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:38,240
After you just announced your fiancée

612
00:53:39,040 --> 00:53:41,320
and you're pretending
like nothing happened?

613
00:53:45,640 --> 00:53:46,480
Mook,

614
00:53:47,840 --> 00:53:49,040
please listen to me.

615
00:53:52,560 --> 00:53:55,840
I'll show my mom
that we really love each other

616
00:53:56,920 --> 00:53:59,320
and that I'll still be able
to do my job well.

617
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:06,560
What about your fiancée?

618
00:54:07,840 --> 00:54:10,520
Please don't drag me into that mess again.

619
00:54:11,480 --> 00:54:13,960
I don't want any more trouble
with your mother.

620
00:54:15,920 --> 00:54:17,920
I just need you to believe in me.

621
00:54:31,640 --> 00:54:33,600
I like to stay realistic.

622
00:54:36,160 --> 00:54:38,040
It might hurt sometimes…

623
00:54:42,920 --> 00:54:44,920
but please don't make me go back again.

624
00:54:52,240 --> 00:54:53,240
Mook.

625
00:55:32,280 --> 00:55:33,400
Ms. Mook!

626
00:55:35,440 --> 00:55:38,400
What's wrong? What's wrong, Ms. Mook?

627
00:55:45,560 --> 00:55:47,160
It's okay.

628
00:56:18,880 --> 00:56:20,760
Where have I seen this kid before?

629
00:56:27,120 --> 00:56:30,280
{\an8}If you have someone else, just admit it.
Is that so hard, Pat?

630
00:56:34,400 --> 00:56:37,080
{\an8}…because my son's made the same mistake.

631
00:56:39,240 --> 00:56:41,640
{\an8}That's why I'm worried about Mr. Thee,

632
00:56:42,200 --> 00:56:44,720
{\an8}since I'm a mother like you.

633
00:56:49,200 --> 00:56:52,000
{\an8}If you can't make Ms. Mook happy,

634
00:56:52,080 --> 00:56:53,960
{\an8}you should let her go.

635
00:56:55,160 --> 00:56:56,960
{\an8}This is my problem.

636
00:56:57,040 --> 00:56:58,480
{\an8}I can deal with it myself.

637
00:57:59,400 --> 00:58:01,680
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

